div.div:
Special detective Kohachi Inugami is sent to investigate a grisly phenomenon involving animal corpses near a remote mountain village. But after meeting a strange boy who agrees to help, he discovers cursed supernatural forces at work. Little by little, Inugami uncovers the truth behind the killings and the boy who may not even be human.
(Source: Funimation)

Eren and his companions in the 104th are assigned to the newly-formed Levi Squad, whose assignment is to keep Eren and Historia safe given Eren's newly-discovered power and Historia's knowledge and pedigree. Levi and Erwin have good reason to be concerned, because the priest of the Church that Hanji had hidden away was found tortured to death, making it clear that the Military Police are involved with the cover-up. Things get more harrowing when the MPs make a move on Erwin and the Levi Squad narrowly avoids capture. Eren is also having problems with his Titan transformation, and a deadly killer has been hired to secure Eren and Historia, one Levi knows all too well from his youth.
(Source: Anime News Network)
Watashi Yori Tsuyoi Otoko to Kekkon Shitai no Seiso Bijin Seito Kaichou (Jitsuha Moto Banchou) no Himitsu wo shiru Kage Kya (Jitsuha Kanojo wo Koeru Saikyou no Yankee)

Akira Kogure, a boy who was a bit of a nerd, accidentally discovered that the beautiful student council president, Shizuka Takasaki, used to be a delinquent girl-gang leader. She said she would only marry a man who was stronger than her. But it turned out that Akira was actually also a former delinquent even stronger than her.
(Source: Fantasia Bunko, translated)

Love is always troubling. You want to have the courage to tell someone how you feel. You want to know who he likes. You want someone to listen to your worries. You want someone to give you a push. I know how you feel, and it hurts. Because I had a past I couldn't forget. And because now I have the "power" to save them.... That's why I, Io Akashi, became an angel. "I've finally found you, the angel of Kuze High." The angel touched the girl's cheek, in order to correct Yuzuki Minato's abnormal tendency to fall in love. This is a slightly mysterious coming-of-age story where memory and love play out softly.
(Source: Dengeki Bunko, translated)
